This paper deals with issues related to internet access and website blocking, which are primarily related to computer networks (cs.NI) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the potential reasons for blocking, which could fall under the categories of cyber law and policy (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
